/ Knowledge Card: Tags
/ border-warning: Matches the yellow "alert" vibe from your original screenshot but cleaner
.card.border-0.shadow-sm.border-start.border-4.border-warning
  .card-body.p-4
    
    / --- Header ---
    .d-flex.align-items-center.mb-4
      .bg-warning-subtle.text-warning-emphasis.rounded-circle.d-flex.align-items-center.justify-content-center.me-3.lh-1{style: "width: 48px; height: 48px"}
        %span.mi.md-24.fill label
      
      %div
        %h5.fw-bold.text-dark.mb-0 Tagging System
        %small.text-secondary Labels for organization, filtering, and special behaviors.

    / --- Content Grid ---
    / g-4: Adds more space between items since we don't have borders to separate them
    .row.g-4
      
      / 1. Public Tags
      .col-lg-6.col-xxl-4
        .d-flex.gap-3
          / Icon: Visual anchor
          .text-warning.flex-shrink-0
            %span.mi.md-24 sell
          
          %div
            %h6.fw-bold.text-dark.mb-1 Public Tags
            %p.small.text-muted.mb-0.lh-sm
              Visible under the problem name. Used for general categorization (e.g., "DP", "Graph"). Supports custom colors.

      / 2. Topic Tags
      .col-lg-6.col-xxl-4
        .d-flex.gap-3
          .text-warning.flex-shrink-0
            %span.mi.md-24 filter_list
          
          %div
            %h6.fw-bold.text-dark.mb-1 Topic Tags
            %p.small.text-muted.mb-0.lh-sm
              Appear at the top of the problem list. Clicking one instantly
              %strong filters
              the view to show only relevant problems.

      / 3. Special Purpose (LLM/Automation)
      .col-lg-6.col-xxl-4
        .d-flex.gap-3
          .text-warning.flex-shrink-0
            %span.mi.md-24 auto_awesome
          
          %div
            %h6.fw-bold.text-dark.mb-1 Special Purpose
            %p.small.text-muted.mb-0.lh-sm
              Annotates problems with extra metadata. 
              %br/
              %span.text-secondary-emphasis.fst-italic Example:
              Tags like 
              %code.small.text-dark LLM Prompt
              can trigger specific automated behaviors.

